comments:
I posted this message to the newsgroup some 3 weeks ago and have not received much response either ways if it is a bug or not.  

Shouldnt tests be usually passing even on the head also, unless some code change has broken the tests ?

As a contributor, if I make a code change,getting a clean run of regression tests gives me a level of confidence that the change didnt atleast break the tests. 

Hence I am logging this bug. 
=======================

Here is my original post to the newsgroup.  Any information that you can provide will be helpful as to why these tests are failing. 

I built the BIRT source from head that I checked out yesterday(01/03) and I ran the org.eclipse.birt.report.engine.tests as Junit plugin tests.

Results: 2 errors and 10 failures.

Is anyone else seeing similar results? Are these known issues..  How can I find out if whether these are expected failures or not.  If they are not expected failures, should I file bugzilla for these - Is that the correct procedure to report this?

Thanks for your help,
Sunitha.

===========================
